1
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:32,991
<i>Ochiyo was a famous singer</i>

2
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:35,744
<i>blessed with a voice</i>
<i>that could move mountains.</i>

3
00:00:35,827 --> 00:00:38,079
<i>It was that way</i>
<i>since she was a little girl.</i>

4
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:41,791
<i>Oh, how that angelic voice</i>

5
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:46,171
<i>brought dreams, beauty, and hope</i>

6
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:50,633
<i>to people drowning in despair</i>
<i>in the aftermath of the war.</i>

7
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:55,138
<i>Man shall not live by bread alone.</i>

8
00:00:56,306 --> 00:01:01,269
<i>This was truly</i>
<i>the simple, raw power of entertainment.</i>

9
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:09,569
<i>Ochiyo and I were actually born</i>
<i>in the same year in Tokyo.</i>

10
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:13,907
<i>It's quite possible</i>
<i>that perhaps we crossed paths back then</i>

11
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:15,784
<i>in the ruins of the city.</i>

12
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:25,168
<i>Wow, that's so beautiful.</i>

13
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:27,754
What an incredible story.

14
00:01:27,837 --> 00:01:29,339
You were saved by Hotta,

15
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:31,382
and you were able to find
and help Shimakura

16
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:33,551
get out of her own horrific situation.

17
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:36,137
The Shimakura angle
makes for an amazing selling point.

18
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:38,723
You could make that the book's
major turning point, couldn't you?

19
00:01:38,807 --> 00:01:39,682
Mm-hmm.

20
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:42,435
What was she like? Shimakura?

21
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:44,771
She was just as you would imagine her.

22
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:47,398
Sensitive and delicate,

23
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,943
pure of heart and soul.

24
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:52,278
Sorry to interrupt, ma'am.

25
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:56,116
You can load those bags over there

26
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:58,827
and use the new carry case for Tiara.

27
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:00,578
Yes, ma'am.

28
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:04,290
You're taking her with you? To Hawaii?

29
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:07,877
Of course. Two weeks is more than enough
to die of loneliness.

30
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:11,131
Right. Tiara is obviously very sensitive,
I take it.

31
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:14,050
Oh, no. It's not her.
I'm the one who would die.

32
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:15,760
Oh.

33
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:18,429
Well, that's very sweet.

34
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,392
We're sorry to bother you
before you leave.

35
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:24,936
It's all right.
I don't have to go for another hour.

36
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:26,646
And we should use all the time we have.

37
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,775
So Shimakura was in debt
to the tune of 400 million yen?

38
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:34,988
More like a billion yen
if we're talking in today's currency.

39
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:38,366
That's crazy, but you got her
out of all that, didn't you?

40
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:39,534
Yes.

41
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:42,871
<i>But I couldn't have done it all on my own,</i>
<i>of course.</i>

42
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:45,206
What the hell is this?

43
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,375
- Is that cash?
- You trying to bribe us?

44
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:51,880
In those cases is 150 million yen.
I'll get straight to the point.

45
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:55,800
If we add up all your claims,
it comes out to 430 million yen.

46
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:58,344
What we're hoping for

47
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:00,930
is that you'll be satisfied
distributing this money

48
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:02,891
equally among yourselves.

49
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:03,975
That's barely a third!

50
00:03:04,058 --> 00:03:05,685
What do we do about the other 300 million?

51
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:07,270
Is this acceptable to you all?

52
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:09,814
- What do you mean by acceptable?
- You're crazy!

53
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:12,692
You can't be serious!
We want what we're owed now!

54
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:15,403
Shimakura, you know
this is a load of bullshit, don't ya?

55
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:32,378
Enough! Would you be all right if
you never heard this woman's songs again?

56
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:33,922
What are we supposed to do with this?

57
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:38,635
'Cause she said herself
that she would rather lay down and die.

58
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:45,016
We all know this woman's music
is a national treasure!

59
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:47,518
And, under normal circumstances,

60
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:50,813
a treasure that no amount of money
could ever purchase.

61
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:54,692
We're hoping

62
00:03:55,568 --> 00:03:58,363
that you all take that into account
when considering this.

63
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:01,574
You should know

64
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:06,829
I'm never one to forget the faces
of those who helped me in times of need.

65
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,585
If you accept this offer,

66
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:16,130
there may be a time in the future
when I can repay the favor.

67
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:20,510
So I'll ask you again now
on my hands and knees.

68
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:28,059
Please!

69
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:42,865
My name is Kazuko Hosoki, and I would like
to announce that starting today,

70
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:46,536
I have been granted conservatorship
over Chiyoko Shimakura.

71
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:49,372
Does this mean you've resolved
her 430 million yen debt?

72
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:52,375
- Has the full amount been repaid?
- No, not the full amount.

73
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:56,587
But, fortunately,
after we explained Shimakura's situation,

74
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,047
the debt collectors understood.

75
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,466
She herself was a victim in all this.

76
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:03,678
And above all else,
we shared the goal of protecting

77
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:06,306
Shimakura's God-given singing voice.

78
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:09,142
As a result, we came to the agreement
of settling the debt

79
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:11,144
at approximately
one-third of its original sum.

80
00:05:11,227 --> 00:05:13,980
Did you pay the debt?
And how is that all gonna work?

81
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:18,359
Shimakura will transfer
to a new company, effective immediately,

82
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:19,944
which I will represent.

83
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:22,697
From there,
I will continue to act as her manager.

84
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:26,034
And through that company, over time,

85
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:28,995
Shimakura will slowly repay me
from her sales proceeds.

86
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:31,497
Shimakura, how do you feel about all this?

87
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,249
I…

88
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:38,254
thought I'd never be able to sing again.

89
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,340
And if I couldn't,

90
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:43,009
I thought I may as well be dead.

91
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:46,471
I didn't know what to do,
but, fortunately,

92
00:05:46,554 --> 00:05:49,349
Kazuko Hosoki came and saved my life.

93
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:55,521
This woman is truly my savior.

94
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,487
It's gonna be okay.

95
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:13,706
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Thank you.

96
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:24,133
Looks kinda empty, doesn't it?

97
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,227
Uh, must be hard…

98
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,228
Hmm.

99
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:37,522
…giving up this life

100
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:40,733
that you fought so hard
for so long to achieve.

101
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:47,657
This place was the only thing
that was always waiting for me.

102
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,668
Listen, Ochiyo.

103
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:04,465
You still have six months
until this place is officially sold.

104
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:07,927
If you put your head down and work hard,

105
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:09,720
you can still buy it back.

106
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,558
Do you really think so?

107
00:07:13,641 --> 00:07:16,686
It's all gonna be about
how much work you put in.

108
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:26,112
Yes, you're right.

109
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:31,284
I'm… gonna give it my all one more time.

110
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:35,455
Good for you.

111
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,206
Thank you.

112
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:42,253
Big sis.

113
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:43,171
What?

114
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:46,674
Well, you know, you're like a big sister.

115
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:49,552
That's… You know
we're the same age, right?

116
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,221
Yeah, but I'm less mature than you.

117
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:56,809
Whatever you say.

118
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:08,404
<i>After that,</i>
<i>we put our heads down and got to work.</i>

119
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:13,993
Everyone, the meet-and-greet
with Chiyoko Shimakura is commencing now!

120
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:18,080
Come on. Let's welcome her out here.
I want you all to gimme a shout!

121
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,749
Welcome!

122
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,959
Welcome!

123
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:24,086
<i>We promoted her anywhere and everywhere.</i>

124
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:27,131
<i>We went from performing</i>
<i>at local venues to even prisons.</i>

125
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:29,217
<i>We took every offer that came our way.</i>

126
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,260
Thank you all for being here today.

127
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:34,347
Okay, so those of you
who wanna shake hands with Ochiyo

128
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:36,474
will have to purchase
this record right here.

129
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:39,185
Only those who purchase this record
can shake hands with Ochiyo,

130
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:40,436
so get your copy now.

131
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,354
Who wants to start?

132
00:08:41,437 --> 00:08:44,065
I'm sure you're all wondering
why we chose to stop in a small town

133
00:08:44,148 --> 00:08:46,567
where there's more chickens
than actual people.

134
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:51,280
Thank you. I inherited
my razor-sharp wit from my sister.

135
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:54,867
The show starts in five minutes.
No talking between songs.

136
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,078
Once you're done,
we gotta jump in the car right away,

137
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:59,288
or we won't make it to the next venue.

138
00:09:06,587 --> 00:09:09,966
<i>It wasn't the kind of job</i>
<i>I was used to, but I did my best.</i>

139
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:11,634
<i>We couldn't afford to be picky with shows</i>

140
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:14,345
<i>if we wanted to buy back</i>
<i>Ochiyo's apartment.</i>

141
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,223
What are you doing?

142
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:20,059
Step on it. You're driving so slow, Hisao.

143
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:23,020
All right. If you want me to step on it…

144
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:26,607
Whoa! Whoa!
You still need to be careful. Hisao!

145
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:45,251
Hey, sis. We need to order more records,

146
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:47,295
or we'll be sold out
by the end of the day.

147
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:50,673
Okay, well, for now,
take these to the members of the fan club.

148
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:52,008
Okay, I'm on it.

149
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:55,678
Ochiyo, here.
You should eat now before the show.

150
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:14,447
Thank you so much for all your help.

151
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,574
- Here's a little something for you.
- Thank you.

152
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:20,369
<i>It wasn't easy juggling the disco</i>
<i>and the tour at the same time.</i>

153
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:21,329
Thank you, ma'am.

154
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:25,207
<i>There were times it got so hard</i>
<i>that I considered throwing in the towel.</i>

155
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:28,461
<i>But…</i>

156
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:32,340
<i>whenever I did start to feel that way,</i>

157
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:35,426
<i>Ochiyo's songs</i>
<i>gave me the strength I needed.</i>

158
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:37,928
<i>I felt like</i>
<i>I needed to keep going for her.</i>

159
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:39,972
<i>And not only that, I wanted to.</i>

160
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:46,437
<i>I wanted the image</i>
<i>of her debt scandal to disappear,</i>

161
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,981
<i>so I made Ochiyo the face of the disco.</i>

162
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:53,819
<i>I was surprised at how easily</i>
<i>the media ate that up. They loved it.</i>

163
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:58,032
CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA COMES BACK FROM HELL!

164
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:03,287
<i>Thanks to our hard work,</i>
<i>Ochiyo's reputation rebounded quickly.</i>

165
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:06,207
<i>The venues got bigger, and soon,</i>

166
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:08,501
<i>television appearances</i>
<i>that seemed impossible</i>

167
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:09,502
<i>were coming our way.</i>

168
00:11:11,295 --> 00:11:12,254
Congratulations.

169
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:17,259
<i>And finally,</i>

170
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:21,013
<i>we were able to buy back</i>
<i>Ochiyo's apartment,</i>

171
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:22,431
<i>which had been put up for auction.</i>

172
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,642
All right. Thanks. Thank you.

173
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,352
Ah.

174
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,979
- Don't worry about those. I got them.
- Hmm.

175
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:32,066
Here, stop it. I got it.
You sure you're good?

176
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,568
- All right, let's get in there.
- Have a good day.

177
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:35,736
Come on. Let's go.

178
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,279
Oh my God. Wow.

179
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,448
In terms of compatibility,
look at our score.

180
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:41,992
- Hmm?
- Ooh, it's off the charts.

181
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:45,371
Just to give you an idea, it's so good,

182
00:11:45,454 --> 00:11:49,375
I should marry Ochiyo right now
and run away with her forever.

183
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,168
If she were a man, that is.

184
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:54,505
Mm. Out of the two of us,
you'd be the man, not me.

185
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:58,634
Ochiyo, I wouldn't worry
about the amateur fortune teller.

186
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:01,887
And the compatibility for you two…

187
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,014
Oof, the worst there is.

188
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,767
If you two get close to each other,
you'll lose everything.

189
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,894
- So better watch it.
- Hmm.

190
00:12:09,478 --> 00:12:10,730
That's all nonsense.

191
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,106
I doubt that.

192
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:14,692
It's all because of Hotta
I was able to find my smile again.

193
00:12:14,775 --> 00:12:17,069
Uh, I thought it was gone for good.

194
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:23,075
Just look at us two sitting here together.

195
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:26,454
For a while,
I never thought I'd smile like this again.

196
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:30,958
You know,
there could be a song in there somewhere.

197
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:33,377
I like it.

198
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:38,007
You should… yeah,
you should write a song for me sometime.

199
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:41,010
No, I couldn't. I'm not a songwriter.

200
00:12:41,093 --> 00:12:44,847
I don't know. I… I think you'd be great.
You're… you're so talented.

201
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:47,725
<i>Chiyoko Shimakura with "Ai no Sazanami."</i>

202
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:55,149
<i>If there really is a god</i>

203
00:12:56,525 --> 00:13:01,030
<i>In this world</i>

204
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:05,159
<i>I wish to die</i>

205
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,038
<i>Held in your arms…</i>

206
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,081
All I want

207
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:15,252
is to sit here and watch you sing forever.

208
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,716
That's very sweet of you.

209
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:24,970
You're a great team.

210
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,556
You two really are like real sisters.

211
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:34,772
<i>Over and over</i>

212
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:36,816
<i>Like the ripples on the water…</i>

213
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,275
You were right before.

214
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:41,570
Our work's really paid off for us.

215
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:44,156
Hmm.

216
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:51,872
<i>But not long after that,</i>
<i>Shimakura left your agency, right?</i>

217
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:55,251
She did, yes.

218
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,627
I made her leave.

219
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,380
But weren't things going really well?

220
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:00,798
Why would you make her leave?

221
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:03,217
According to this article,

222
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:05,928
Shimakura actually wanted
to stay with your agency.

223
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:10,182
CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA REPAYS HER DEBT
AND CHANGES AGENCIES

224
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,104
This takes me back.

225
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,818
All good things
must come to an end sometime.

226
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:24,321
I was still an amateur
in the music industry,

227
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:28,158
and I had already started
studying fortune-telling.

228
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:30,744
I wanted to master it someday.

229
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:35,791
So once Ochiyo's debts were all paid off,

230
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,752
it made sense for us
to go our separate ways.

231
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:43,007
Ochiyo is still as relevant today
as she was back then.

232
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:46,635
So it turns out it was the right decision.

233
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:50,306
It didn't make it any easier though.

234
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:54,518
Yeah, it must've been really hard,
seeing as you two were like sisters.

235
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:58,939
You know, I don't have much
of a relationship with my sisters.

236
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:03,527
And that could be why
I loved Ochiyo so much at the time.

237
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:10,159
You never told me
what your brother is up to these days.

238
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,118
Hisao?

239
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,370
Yeah. He ran the clubs with you back then.

240
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:15,956
I can only imagine you two
were the closest in your family.

241
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,500
If he's around,
I'd love to hear from him, if possible.

242
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:22,004
I'm not exactly sure
where he is these days.

243
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,216
A lot happened.

244
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,511
Sorry to interrupt.

245
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:30,971
Ma'am?

246
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:34,350
- Well, we should get going too.
- Oh, of course.

247
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,229
Minori.

248
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,608
I just can't wait
to read the completed book.

249
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:46,320
Oh. Well, I still have lots
I want to cover with you,

250
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,656
but I do think it's time for me to begin.

251
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:49,740
You do?

252
00:15:50,574 --> 00:15:52,743
I'm not trying to rush you.

253
00:15:52,826 --> 00:15:55,537
It's just probably best to write
and publish it sooner than later.

254
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,248
You've gotta strike while the iron's hot.

255
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:00,584
We'll take that into account, ma'am.

256
00:16:57,558 --> 00:17:04,565
SELF-PORTRAIT OF A WOMAN
BY MINORI UOZUMI

257
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,902
All right, I'm running late.

258
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:11,363
- Minori? I'm heading out now.
- Okay.

259
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:14,825
Make sure you lock up behind me.
It's not exactly the safest around here.

260
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:16,910
- Okay, say have a good day to Grandma.
- Mommy?

261
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:19,329
- Uh-huh?
- I want a rice ball.

262
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:23,625
What? You said you wanted bread.
Here, look, it's good. I promise.

263
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:27,713
- Good morning, everybody!
- Good morning.

264
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:30,382
- Thank you so much. Reina.
- I wanna go outside. It's hot in here.

265
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:32,593
Bye, Mom!

266
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:33,510
Bye.

267
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:13,926
KAZUKO FACED THE CRUEL NATURE OF WAR…

268
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:18,972
THE PAIN OF THE WOUND COMFORTED HER.

269
00:18:24,394 --> 00:18:30,067
TRUE ANGER CAN BE
SO INTENSE, PAINFUL, AND LONELY.

270
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:35,614
THE SHARP FLASHES REFLECTED
FROM THE MIRROR BALL

271
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:38,784
ONTO KAZUKO'S BODY.

272
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:43,288
"THIS IS MY WORLD."

273
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:58,262
I WANT TO TRY COMPETING ON A BIG STAGE.

274
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:08,814
KAZUKO HOSOKI'S BROTHER ARRESTED
FOR BLACKMAILING TOWN COUNCIL CHAIRMAN

275
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:10,482
THE TRUTH AS TOLD TO US

276
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:26,165
Hey, Reina.
Your mommy's here to pick you up.

277
00:19:27,374 --> 00:19:29,668
Reina, did you hear me? Your mommy's here.

278
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:31,503
Reina.

279
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:33,964
Okay, bye.

280
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,433
Yes, hello. Minori speaking.

281
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,310
<i>Are you the novelist?</i>

282
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,563
Yes, that's correct.

283
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:53,317
<i>My name is Hosoki.</i>
<i>I heard you wanted to speak to me?</i>

284
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:54,651
Hoso…

285
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:57,029
You're Hisao?

286
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:00,991
<i>You tried to contact me Friday, right?</i>

287
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:02,701
<i>I didn't know</i>
<i>how to get in touch with you,</i>

288
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:05,454
<i>so someone in your editorial department</i>
<i>gave me your number.</i>

289
00:20:07,915 --> 00:20:09,666
<i>You wanted to ask about my sister?</i>

290
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:13,754
<i>If you're still interested,</i>
<i>why don't you come over to my place?</i>

291
00:20:13,837 --> 00:20:15,923
<i>I'm happy to answer any questions.</i>

292
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:33,440
Come in.

293
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:37,486
Oh, yes. Thank you very much.

294
00:20:45,869 --> 00:20:48,288
As you can see, I have a real sweet tooth.

295
00:20:49,957 --> 00:20:51,291
I can't get enough.

296
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,919
Mont Blanc is my favorite.

297
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,922
I know.

298
00:20:58,048 --> 00:21:00,300
I saw you on a magazine cover.

299
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:02,803
Oh!

300
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:05,681
KAZUKO HOSOKI'S BROTHER ARRESTED
THE TRUTH AS TOLD TO US

301
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,557
You've got some nerve, you know that?

302
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:09,101
Excuse me?

303
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:12,646
Do you usually show something like that
to the person you're talking to?

304
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:16,108
Oh, I'm sorry.

305
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,736
No, I'm just kiddin'.

306
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:23,865
Ah, you'll need to be that ballsy
if you wanna deal with my sister.

307
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,325
She's a tough cookie.

308
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,995
How are things between the two of you?

309
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:29,997
I was disowned.

310
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,041
Was that Kazuko's decision?

311
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:34,960
There was the article,

312
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,212
and then the police got involved.

313
00:21:37,879 --> 00:21:38,880
I guess being a celebrity,

314
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:41,842
Kazuko thought it was best
to wash her hands of me.

315
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:44,261
Oh, I see.

316
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:48,348
You're writing a book
about her life, right?

317
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:51,852
How much have you heard?

318
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:55,022
Up to the point
where she paid off Shimakura's debt.

319
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:58,108
- Hmm.
- I heard Kazuko and her were like sisters.

320
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,067
They were so close.

321
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:05,824
My sister told you that, didn't she?

322
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:08,910
Yeah. She said it wasn't easy

323
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,413
when Shimakura left the agency.

324
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:23,050
This must be the story
where Kazuko saw Shimakura

325
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:27,679
about to jump off a bridge somewhere
until my sister saved her, right?

326
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:28,764
Yeah.

327
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:31,141
And then she became her manager

328
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:33,643
and told her
to put her head down and get to work.

329
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:34,728
Yes.

330
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,271
Did you hear about Hotta too?

331
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:37,814
Yes, I did.

332
00:22:37,898 --> 00:22:40,859
Hotta helped your sister
when she paid off Shimakura's debt.

333
00:22:40,942 --> 00:22:41,902
And

334
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:45,614
that they bought back
Shimakura's apartment.

335
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:46,531
Yes.

336
00:23:05,258 --> 00:23:06,593
But you know

337
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:09,221
that that whole story is a lie?

338
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:13,350
- What?
- The whole thing's fake.

339
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:16,269
You bought it completely, didn't you?

340
00:23:16,937 --> 00:23:18,814
Don't worry. You're one of many.

341
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:22,317
Would you like to

342
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:25,320
hear what really happened?

343
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:35,705
<i>The disco that my sister and Hotta started</i>

344
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:37,833
<i>was a big success at first.</i>

345
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:41,002
<i>But after three years,</i>
<i>business had completely tanked.</i>

346
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:43,213
I built this place from the ground up!

347
00:23:43,296 --> 00:23:45,507
I'm not just about to let it go!

348
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:48,593
<i>And when their finances</i>
<i>started to plummet,</i>

349
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:50,554
<i>so did their relationship.</i>

350
00:23:50,637 --> 00:23:53,598
<i>Just goes to show how shallow</i>
<i>their relationship was to begin with.</i>

351
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:56,351
What's with the attitude?
You've got a lot to say for a poor yakuza

352
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:58,145
who's got nothing without my money.

353
00:23:58,645 --> 00:23:59,980
Don't act like you're in charge!

354
00:24:00,063 --> 00:24:01,606
You've got some nerve talking back to me

355
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,567
when the only reason
we're in this situation is…

356
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:07,571
<i>And it was one night during one</i>
<i>of their many fights that the phone rang.</i>

357
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:09,948
Acting like it's never your fault.
You're perfect.

358
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:11,908
Well, you know what,
this disco was supposed to--

359
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:13,577
You should probably get that!

360
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,871
- Answer it, why don't you?
- No, you answer the damn phone!

361
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,080
Hisao, answer the phone!

362
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:18,123
Uh, sure.

363
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:21,251
This is Manhattan.

364
00:24:21,918 --> 00:24:24,212
Yes, please hold for a moment.

365
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:27,340
Hotta, it's for you.

366
00:24:27,424 --> 00:24:30,302
Um, he says his name is Yabe?

367
00:24:31,428 --> 00:24:32,387
Yabe-san?

368
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:33,722
Yes.

369
00:24:38,268 --> 00:24:40,187
Yes. It's Hotta.

370
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:42,314
<i>Turns out this Yabe guy was a fixer</i>

371
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:45,525
<i>who had connections in the yakuza</i>
<i>and entertainment industry.</i>

372
00:24:45,609 --> 00:24:48,028
<i>He was also</i>
<i>Shimakura's guardian at the time.</i>

373
00:24:49,779 --> 00:24:50,739
Chiyoko Shimakura?

374
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:52,866
<i>He wanted Hotta</i>
<i>to help him protect Shimakura</i>

375
00:24:52,949 --> 00:24:55,118
<i>from some debt collectors</i>
<i>who were harassing her.</i>

376
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:56,369
I understand.

377
00:24:58,079 --> 00:25:00,499
I never thought
he'd leave me with all that debt.

378
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:04,211
<i>That's really how my sister</i>
<i>and Shimakura met each other.</i>

379
00:25:04,294 --> 00:25:06,046
I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.

380
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:09,799
<i>All that stuff about Kazuko</i>
<i>spotting her on the bridge is a lie.</i>

381
00:25:09,883 --> 00:25:11,009
I could really use some help.

382
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:12,427
<i>Like a shark in the water,</i>

383
00:25:12,511 --> 00:25:14,930
<i>my sister</i>
<i>could smell opportunity a mile away.</i>

384
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:16,139
<i>Even under all that debt,</i>

385
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:18,892
<i>this was still</i>
<i>the one and only Chiyoko Shimakura.</i>

386
00:25:18,975 --> 00:25:22,354
<i>It was as if an angel</i>
<i>had sent her a gift from above.</i>

387
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:24,189
A long time ago,

388
00:25:25,106 --> 00:25:27,108
I went through the same thing as you.

389
00:25:28,652 --> 00:25:30,779
And you know who got me through all that?

390
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:32,322
You're looking at him.

391
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:35,367
It's gonna be okay.

392
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:38,411
We'll get you through all this.
Don't worry.

393
00:25:40,163 --> 00:25:42,123
<i>Hotta called in all the favors he had left</i>

394
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:45,377
<i>and managed</i>
<i>to scrape together 150 million yen.</i>

395
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:47,212
<i>Then they put on a show.</i>

396
00:25:47,295 --> 00:25:49,506
<i>My sister came up with the whole charade.</i>

397
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:52,133
<i>Hotta may not have liked it,</i>
<i>but he was struggling too.</i>

398
00:25:52,217 --> 00:25:53,718
<i>He had no choice but to play along.</i>

399
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:56,680
Would you be all right if you never heard
any of this woman's songs again?

400
00:25:56,763 --> 00:25:58,765
<i>Even though</i>
<i>his financial situation was dire,</i>

401
00:25:58,848 --> 00:26:01,309
<i>he was still the boss</i>
<i>of a major crime family.</i>

402
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:03,228
So I'll ask you again now
on my hands and knees!

403
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:05,772
<i>So they knew</i>
<i>when he put on that song and dance,</i>

404
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:08,275
<i>the collectors would have no choice</i>
<i>but to give in.</i>

405
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:10,902
<i>They were terrified</i>
<i>of what would happen if they refused him.</i>

406
00:26:10,986 --> 00:26:11,820
Please!

407
00:26:11,903 --> 00:26:14,489
<i>Through all the noise,</i>
<i>the threat was clear.</i>

408
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:21,496
<i>Shimakura was especially moved</i>
<i>by my sister and Hotta's performance.</i>

409
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,206
Shimakura, how do you feel about all this?

410
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:25,125
I thought I'd never be able to sing again.

411
00:26:25,208 --> 00:26:28,336
And if I couldn't…
I thought I might as well be dead.

412
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:30,839
<i>After that, she was putty in their hands.</i>

413
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:33,091
<i>She resolved to work</i>
<i>as hard as she could for them.</i>

414
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:36,928
Kazuko Hosoki came and saved my life.

415
00:26:38,138 --> 00:26:42,142
This woman… is truly my savior.

416
00:26:42,225 --> 00:26:44,853
<i>Suddenly, my sister became</i>
<i>the talk of the town.</i>

417
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:47,689
<i>The savior who rescued</i>
<i>the great Chiyoko Shimakura</i>

418
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:49,441
<i>from the brink of death.</i>

419
00:26:49,524 --> 00:26:52,027
<i>In doing that,</i>
<i>she perfectly laid the groundwork</i>

420
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:54,279
<i>to siphon money from Shimakura.</i>

421
00:26:56,323 --> 00:26:59,826
<i>And that great comeback story</i>
<i>of them toughing it out on the road?</i>

422
00:26:59,909 --> 00:27:01,620
<i>Even that's bogus.</i>

423
00:27:01,703 --> 00:27:05,415
<i>Hotta used the local yakuza syndicates</i>
<i>to secure the venues for nothing.</i>

424
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,834
<i>It was all a big sham.</i>

425
00:27:18,345 --> 00:27:21,765
<i>Of course, as soon as Kazuko</i>
<i>made Shimakura the face of the disco,</i>

426
00:27:22,265 --> 00:27:23,516
<i>the media ate it up.</i>

427
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:27,020
<i>The public immediately went crazy,</i>
<i>and business soared again.</i>

428
00:27:27,103 --> 00:27:28,938
<i>It was definitely seedy stuff,</i>

429
00:27:29,439 --> 00:27:31,274
<i>but I have to give it to my sister.</i>

430
00:27:31,358 --> 00:27:32,651
<i>It was impressive.</i>

431
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:36,655
<i>Hotta, on the other hand,</i>
<i>was an old-fashioned yakuza.</i>

432
00:27:36,738 --> 00:27:39,199
<i>He valued duty and humanity.</i>

433
00:27:39,282 --> 00:27:41,910
<i>Over time, he grew to hate</i>
<i>what my sister was doing.</i>

434
00:27:42,410 --> 00:27:44,746
<i>Hate how she was exploiting Shimakura.</i>

435
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:46,623
CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA COMES BACK FROM HELL!

436
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:48,166
Hmm.

437
00:27:52,128 --> 00:27:53,463
Congratulations.

438
00:27:57,092 --> 00:27:59,969
<i>The plan worked better</i>
<i>than even my sister could've imagined.</i>

439
00:28:00,053 --> 00:28:02,013
<i>Shimakura was bigger than ever.</i>

440
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:05,767
<i>The calls for big jobs and events</i>
<i>kept coming in.</i>

441
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:08,561
<i>I can only imagine</i>
<i>how ecstatic my sister was.</i>

442
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:17,612
In the end, it was always about money.

443
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:22,075
My sister never cared about Shimakura.
She just wanted a cash cow.

444
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:26,121
The entire narrative
that Kazuko wanted to help her was a lie.

445
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:29,374
My sister took her own experience
of being exploited

446
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:32,001
and used it to learn
how to exploit others.

447
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:39,217
Wait, but I… I thought after she paid
your sister back the 150 million yen,

448
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:41,845
Shimakura became independent again.

449
00:28:41,928 --> 00:28:43,930
So Kazuko couldn't have made
that much money off her.

450
00:28:44,013 --> 00:28:46,141
You kids today really are naive.

451
00:28:47,016 --> 00:28:49,352
Shimakura was a big-time star back then.

452
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:53,231
No matter what venue, big or small,
she got at least two million yen.

453
00:28:53,314 --> 00:28:55,442
And at some,
she made closer to three or four million.

454
00:28:55,525 --> 00:28:58,611
My sister was relentless
and made her do 200 shows a year.

455
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:01,072
You do the math.

456
00:29:03,116 --> 00:29:05,910
- Uh…
- That's 400 million yen a year in total.

457
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:07,036
At least.

458
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:09,581
So if my sister
just wanted back that 150 million,

459
00:29:09,664 --> 00:29:11,124
it wouldn't have been tough.

460
00:29:11,666 --> 00:29:12,876
You're saying…

461
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:17,297
Shimakura, she was young and naive.

462
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:19,716
She didn't realize
she was being manipulated.

463
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:21,259
But finally, after three years,

464
00:29:21,342 --> 00:29:24,137
she was able to piece together
what my sister had done.

465
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:28,141
That's the real reason
they parted ways in the end.

466
00:29:28,224 --> 00:29:32,979
Okay, but Shimakura called your sister
her savior at the time, didn't she?

467
00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:34,773
Why wouldn't she tell everyone--

468
00:29:34,856 --> 00:29:36,733
That's how she made peace with it.

469
00:29:38,276 --> 00:29:39,903
It was her way of

470
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:41,863
calling it even.

471
00:29:58,671 --> 00:29:59,547
Thank you.

472
00:30:42,048 --> 00:30:42,966
Hey.

473
00:30:44,050 --> 00:30:47,011
What do you say
we go on a trip together sometime soon?

474
00:30:47,762 --> 00:30:49,681
Like to Hawaii or Guam.

475
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:53,226
Celebrate bringing our business
back from the dead.

476
00:30:54,978 --> 00:30:57,689
No, thanks. You can go on your own.

477
00:30:58,189 --> 00:31:00,358
What is with you recently?

478
00:31:01,568 --> 00:31:03,152
You and Ochiyo have work to do.

479
00:31:03,236 --> 00:31:07,115
Ochiyo can handle things
by herself for a week or two.

480
00:31:08,199 --> 00:31:09,117
Come on.

481
00:31:09,617 --> 00:31:10,451
Yeah?

482
00:31:10,952 --> 00:31:12,537
It'll be good for us too.

483
00:31:20,628 --> 00:31:22,130
You're back late.

484
00:31:22,922 --> 00:31:24,257
You better rest up.

485
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:25,884
Go to bed.

486
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:31,472
I haven't even had dinner.

487
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:33,725
Didn't you eat while you were out?

488
00:31:35,602 --> 00:31:37,020
I was too busy.

489
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:40,732
Then I'll make you something.

490
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:42,692
Go take a bath.

491
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:49,657
It's pretty late, so make sure
it's something easy on the stomach.

492
00:31:49,741 --> 00:31:51,659
Something filling, but not too heavy.

493
00:31:52,368 --> 00:31:53,786
God, you're spoiled.

494
00:31:54,412 --> 00:31:55,538
You're gonna shut up

495
00:31:55,622 --> 00:31:58,666
and eat whatever I feel like
putting in front of you.

496
00:32:07,008 --> 00:32:07,842
Um…

497
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:11,554
How much do I have left

498
00:32:12,513 --> 00:32:13,723
to pay you back?

499
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:21,189
I've been working pretty hard.
I must be getting close.

500
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:25,234
I didn't wanna worry you.

501
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:27,946
You've got enough on your plate,
but you should know that

502
00:32:28,738 --> 00:32:30,073
I actually

503
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:34,577
found out about another debt
you owe a few months ago.

504
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:37,497
What?

505
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:42,168
Yes, but we took care of it,
so there's no reason for you to worry.

506
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:47,298
How much is it?

507
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:49,342
This new debt.

508
00:32:52,553 --> 00:32:54,138
100 million yen.

509
00:32:59,018 --> 00:33:00,436
That can't be.

510
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:05,525
I'm sorry to be the bearer of bad news,
but your man was hopeless.

511
00:33:05,608 --> 00:33:08,069
Handing out promissory notes
like they're candy.

512
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:11,614
I wouldn't be shocked
if more surprise debts turn up.

513
00:33:11,698 --> 00:33:13,491
This will be the last one.

514
00:33:16,953 --> 00:33:18,079
I'm sure of it.

515
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:33,886
Ochiyo, great job tonight.

516
00:33:33,970 --> 00:33:35,513
Thank you, you too.

517
00:33:36,931 --> 00:33:38,307
Shimakura-san.

518
00:33:39,517 --> 00:33:40,935
Oh, Sawamura!

519
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:43,187
My gosh, it's been a long time.

520
00:33:43,271 --> 00:33:45,773
Yes, it's good to see you. How are things?

521
00:33:45,857 --> 00:33:47,567
- They're good. I've got a new client.
- Great.

522
00:33:47,650 --> 00:33:48,818
So I'm here promoting her.

523
00:33:48,901 --> 00:33:50,445
- Very nice.
- Mm-hmm.

524
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:55,658
Is Kazuko here, or is it just you?

525
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:57,994
We're working separately tonight.

526
00:33:58,077 --> 00:33:59,746
Arriving in studio with Saijo!

527
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:02,582
Hey.

528
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:05,001
Can we chat?

529
00:34:06,544 --> 00:34:07,962
It makes no sense.

530
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:11,257
After three years,
this debt just shows up out of the blue?

531
00:34:13,176 --> 00:34:16,971
You're playing big venues
and doing TV gigs like you used to.

532
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:20,975
And you're also doing
those six-month-long regional tours.

533
00:34:26,522 --> 00:34:29,192
How much do you get paid
for each of those regional shows?

534
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:33,154
I actually don't know.

535
00:34:34,030 --> 00:34:37,492
They tell me
not to worry about that stuff.

536
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:40,620
I just cannot believe
that they're keeping this from you.

537
00:34:41,662 --> 00:34:44,457
Well, I do get a monthly allowance, so…

538
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:45,833
And how much is that?

539
00:34:47,877 --> 00:34:49,045
The allowance?

540
00:34:51,214 --> 00:34:52,632
30,000 yen.

541
00:34:55,009 --> 00:34:56,344
Okay, Shimakura-san.

542
00:34:56,427 --> 00:34:58,846
I want you to listen to me very carefully.

543
00:35:01,557 --> 00:35:06,813
You are a massive star who's appeared
on the <i>Kohaku </i>20 years in a row now.

544
00:35:07,647 --> 00:35:10,024
Unless it's volunteer work or charity,

545
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:12,777
you should be getting minimum
two million yen per show.

546
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:14,695
And realistically, more like five.

547
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:19,158
And if you're doing 100 shows a year,
that's roughly two to 500 million yen…

548
00:35:59,740 --> 00:36:00,825
Perfect.

549
00:36:12,503 --> 00:36:14,922
Jesus. You scared the hell outta me.

550
00:36:15,423 --> 00:36:17,216
I didn't know you were home.

551
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:18,801
How did the recording go?

552
00:36:23,639 --> 00:36:26,309
Okay.
Well, I'm going to dinner with a friend.

553
00:36:26,392 --> 00:36:28,102
You get yourself some takeout.

554
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:29,478
My throat hurts.

555
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:31,564
Huh?

556
00:36:32,148 --> 00:36:34,817
I think I might've strained my voice
at the recording today.

557
00:36:34,901 --> 00:36:37,195
I'm not sure I should be eating takeout.

558
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:39,655
Can you make me
some rice porridge or something?

559
00:36:39,739 --> 00:36:41,949
You can make rice porridge yourself.

560
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:42,950
Please.

561
00:36:44,785 --> 00:36:46,787
I can't even crack an egg properly.

562
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:48,706
You know that.

563
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:57,006
You're gonna make me late for my meeting.

564
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:22,281
Actually…

565
00:37:24,075 --> 00:37:25,868
What do you want now?

566
00:37:28,454 --> 00:37:29,705
Could you also,

567
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:33,960
while you're out, get me some black tea?

568
00:37:34,043 --> 00:37:37,171
I'd also like ginger and honey in it.
So you'd have to pick that up too.

569
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:42,593
What the hell has gotten into you?

570
00:37:43,511 --> 00:37:46,222
I don't know who you think
you're talking to right now,

571
00:37:46,305 --> 00:37:47,932
but you need to fix your attitude.

572
00:37:48,015 --> 00:37:49,392
I am not your maid.

573
00:37:53,688 --> 00:37:54,814
Yeah, well…

574
00:37:57,108 --> 00:37:59,318
I make a lot of money with this voice.

575
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:02,071
So if this voice doesn't work,

576
00:38:02,571 --> 00:38:03,823
you make no money.

577
00:38:05,241 --> 00:38:06,409
And if you don't,

578
00:38:07,118 --> 00:38:10,079
you'd have to stop buying
fancy things like that coat.

579
00:38:12,456 --> 00:38:13,833
Okay.

580
00:38:15,042 --> 00:38:17,837
Why don't you just say
what you really wanna say?

581
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:26,429
How much have I earned?

582
00:38:28,514 --> 00:38:31,851
- How much in the past three years?
- You already know that.

583
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:33,477
150 million yen.

584
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:36,689
Really? 'Cause I asked someone
who knows this business,

585
00:38:36,772 --> 00:38:38,858
and they told me
that I earned ten times that!

586
00:38:39,984 --> 00:38:43,821
I paid off the 150 million yen I owed you
in the first six months, didn't I?

587
00:38:45,698 --> 00:38:47,158
Poor baby.

588
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:50,328
I think someone's been lying to you again.

589
00:38:51,871 --> 00:38:53,748
You didn't learn from last time?

590
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:56,709
I think you're the one
who's been lying to me.

591
00:38:58,377 --> 00:38:59,211
You are,

592
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:00,838
aren't you?

593
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:04,091
You've been lying to me
from the start of all this.

594
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:08,346
Using me to try and get rich!
You lied about the new debt too!

595
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:11,599
Ochiyo.

596
00:39:13,642 --> 00:39:15,061
The only thing

597
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:18,064
that you're any good at is singing.

598
00:39:18,564 --> 00:39:21,150
So maybe you should just shut up
and do it.

599
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:25,696
You cried like a baby and said you'd die
if you couldn't sing, right?

600
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:29,241
Remind me again who made that possible.

601
00:39:29,325 --> 00:39:31,410
I did that for you!

602
00:39:32,912 --> 00:39:36,874
So not only did I
take on that debt for you,

603
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:40,336
according to you,
I saved your life altogether!

604
00:39:41,087 --> 00:39:43,005
So how dare you speak this way

605
00:39:43,089 --> 00:39:45,883
to someone you yourself admit
did all of that!

606
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:49,011
Instead of acting like a spoiled child,

607
00:39:49,095 --> 00:39:52,973
you should be singing anywhere, cabarets,
classrooms, high schools, graduations!

608
00:39:53,057 --> 00:39:55,101
And you should be grateful for that!

609
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:01,315
You took…

610
00:40:03,526 --> 00:40:05,111
advantage of me…

611
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:08,197
and my love for singing.

612
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:10,449
Your love for singing?

613
00:40:10,533 --> 00:40:12,993
My God, how deluded can you get?

614
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:17,581
Do you have any idea
what I could do to you?

615
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:22,461
I could make it so you never have
the chance to sing anywhere again.

616
00:40:24,046 --> 00:40:27,758
So I'd keep that in mind
the next time you're feeling brave.

617
00:40:42,857 --> 00:40:45,526
Why would you do this to me?

618
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:52,408
Get out of here!

619
00:40:53,075 --> 00:40:54,493
I want you to leave!

620
00:40:54,577 --> 00:40:56,162
This is my house!

621
00:40:56,245 --> 00:40:57,746
You're the one who's leaving.

622
00:40:58,831 --> 00:41:00,499
This isn't your apartment.

623
00:41:02,001 --> 00:41:02,835
Huh?

624
00:41:02,918 --> 00:41:05,588
I'm the one who bought it
at the auction, remember?

625
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:07,965
It's in my name.

626
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:14,472
And, boy,
did I get it for a great bargain.

627
00:41:19,477 --> 00:41:22,188
Your stupidity made things so much easier.

628
00:41:38,454 --> 00:41:40,539
I want you gone when I get back.

629
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,250
So I'd start packing.

630
00:42:39,682 --> 00:42:40,724
Ochiyo.

631
00:42:45,354 --> 00:42:46,772
I spoke to Kazuko.

632
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:50,651
I arranged somewhere
for you to stay for a while.

633
00:42:51,485 --> 00:42:52,861
I'll take you. Come on.

634
00:43:00,619 --> 00:43:02,454
I won't make any excuses.

635
00:43:06,166 --> 00:43:07,042
But…

636
00:43:10,004 --> 00:43:12,298
I truly did love hearing you sing.

637
00:43:13,340 --> 00:43:14,758
That was never a lie.

638
00:43:16,635 --> 00:43:18,053
I hope you know that.

639
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:26,604
Just so you know,

640
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,440
I never wanted to do this.

641
00:43:30,232 --> 00:43:31,191
So,

642
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:35,279
if there's ever anything I can do for you,
I'm here.

643
00:43:40,576 --> 00:43:41,577
Really?

644
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:43,829
'Course.

645
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:48,792
Actually, there may be something.

646
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:52,463
All right.

647
00:43:53,839 --> 00:43:54,673
I'll do it.

648
00:43:57,259 --> 00:43:58,093
Good.

649
00:44:02,056 --> 00:44:03,432
It's something big.

650
00:44:04,767 --> 00:44:06,268
I hope that's all right.

651
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:23,340
<i>Ending my life</i>

652
00:47:24,132 --> 00:47:27,553
<i>Even the roses and cosmos</i>

653
00:47:28,345 --> 00:47:31,765
<i>Told me to wither away</i>

654
00:47:32,558 --> 00:47:35,769
<i>I cut my hair short</i>

655
00:47:36,645 --> 00:47:40,232
<i>And bit down on my pinky</i>

656
00:47:40,858 --> 00:47:47,865
<i>I'd spend my days crying</i>
<i>And blaming myself</i>

657
00:47:48,699 --> 00:47:52,870
<i>Hey, isn't youth funny?</i>

658
00:47:52,953 --> 00:47:56,915
<i>Hey, isn't youth absurd?</i>

659
00:47:56,999 --> 00:48:01,753
<i>Tears flow over funny stories</i>

660
00:48:01,837 --> 00:48:08,844
<i>And in those tears</i>
<i>Is an abundance of youth</i>

661
00:48:10,220 --> 00:48:13,265
<i>Life is full of ups and downs</i>

662
00:48:14,474 --> 00:48:17,519
<i>Men come in all sorts</i>

663
00:48:18,687 --> 00:48:25,694
<i>Women come in all sorts too</i>
<i>And they all bloom wildly</i>

664
00:48:30,824 --> 00:48:34,328
Your song, "Jinsei Iroiro."
Man, it's just beautiful.

665
00:48:34,411 --> 00:48:36,163
My wife and I really love that one.

666
00:48:36,246 --> 00:48:38,832
And, you know, I've been
to many of your shows over the years.

667
00:48:38,916 --> 00:48:42,294
Actually, my wife and I's third date
was your Tokyo tour in '91.

668
00:48:42,377 --> 00:48:43,754
One of the best nights of my life.

669
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:45,213
Excuse me, Shimakura-san!

670
00:48:45,297 --> 00:48:47,633
Can I just have a moment
of your time for a quick question?

671
00:48:47,716 --> 00:48:49,968
I'm writing a novel about Kazuko Hosoki.

672
00:48:50,052 --> 00:48:51,887
I was wondering
if you could tell me the truth

673
00:48:51,970 --> 00:48:53,221
about what happened between you.

674
00:48:53,305 --> 00:48:56,308
- I'm sorry, but you just can't ambush--
- What is it you wanna know, young lady?

675
00:49:00,062 --> 00:49:03,190
Back when you were tricked
into taking on a lot of debt,

676
00:49:03,273 --> 00:49:05,984
you met Kazuko Hosoki by chance,
and she saved you.

677
00:49:06,068 --> 00:49:07,110
Is that true?

678
00:49:13,367 --> 00:49:14,493
Yes, it's true.

679
00:49:15,410 --> 00:49:17,955
Kazuko Hosoki is my savior.

680
00:49:19,206 --> 00:49:20,666
If it wasn't for her,

681
00:49:21,166 --> 00:49:24,127
I probably never would've been able
to continue singing.

682
00:49:25,796 --> 00:49:26,630
Yeah.

683
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:29,383
A certain someone said

684
00:49:29,466 --> 00:49:32,511
that she and her husband
took advantage of you for years.

685
00:49:32,594 --> 00:49:36,181
They made you do all those shows
and then pocketed all the profits.

686
00:49:37,099 --> 00:49:38,892
But even if all of that did happen,

687
00:49:39,393 --> 00:49:41,853
it still doesn't change the fact
that Kazuko saved my life.

688
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:46,817
Even if she deceived you to do it?

689
00:49:51,113 --> 00:49:55,409
Sometimes it's better to be deceived
and not know about it.

690
00:50:00,539 --> 00:50:01,832
Good luck with your book.

691
00:50:03,208 --> 00:50:04,209
Uh, this way.

692
00:50:15,178 --> 00:50:20,934
INCOMING CALL
HOSOKI-SAN

693
00:51:08,231 --> 00:51:10,650
CHIYOKO SHIMAKURA REPAYS HER DEBT
AND CHANGES AGENCIES
